race.comment: Market has this a race in three and it's hard to be against that idea on form and figures. DARTH INVADER (2) brings strong figures from Victoria and has switched to the Currie yard on a 33-day return. Goes in the fresh side and owns a trial win here. Finds a suitable assignment and can find winning form. BOMBARD (6) peaks for the premier metro stable and has been racing in stronger Maidens. She maps well, and a 1.5kg claimer rides off a freshen. Given some time following her last start at Ipswich and this looks well within her grasp. DR FARTHING (10) creates plenty of interest being the unknown commodity. His trials coming into this have been exceptional and the fact he's locally trained is a big tick for him. Needs a touch of luck, but he looks to have some class about him. Bit of a raffle between the rest, so maybe SOUTHAMPTON NICCO (5) from an inside draw first-up can be thereabouts.
